+# `@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus`
+
+The Reckoner — foundation apparatus for Reckoner-gated writ scheduling. Provides
+a kit-static petitioner registry, `guild.json` configuration parsing, priority
+dimension types with default-filling, and the `petition()` / `withdraw()` helper
+APIs. Sits between the Clerk (writ lifecycle) and the Spider (writ dispatch):
+petitioners post writs that stay in `new` phase until the Reckoner evaluates their
+priority and decides whether to approve, defer, or decline them.
+
+See also: [`docs/architecture/petitioner-registration.md`](../../../docs/architecture/petitioner-registration.md).
+
+---
+
+## Installation
+
+Add the apparatus to `guild.json`:
+
+```json
+{
+  "plugins": [
+    "@shardworks/clerk-apparatus",
+    "@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus"
+  ]
+}
+```
+
+---
+
+## API
+
+```typescript
+interface ReckonerApi {
+  /**
+   * Post a writ in `new` phase with Reckoner ext set correctly.
+   *
+   * Validates dimension values, applies defaults for omitted priority
+   * dimensions, validates source against the registry (per
+   * `enforceRegistration`), and calls `clerk.post()` + `clerk.setWritExt()`
+   * in one ergonomic call.
+   *
+   * Returns the persisted WritDoc with phase:'new' and ext.reckoner populated.
+   */
+  petition(request: PetitionRequest): Promise<WritDoc>;
+
+  /**
+   * Withdraw a held writ by transitioning it to `cancelled`.
+   * Thin wrapper around `clerk.transition(writId, 'cancelled', { resolution: reason })`.
+   */
+  withdraw(writId: string, reason?: string): Promise<WritDoc>;
+}
+```
+
+Retrieve the API from the guild:
+
+```typescript
+import { guild } from '@shardworks/nexus-core';
+import type { ReckonerApi } from '@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus';
+
+const reckoner = guild().apparatus<ReckonerApi>('reckoner');
+```
+
+### `petition()` — post a Reckoner-gated writ
+
+```typescript
+const writ = await reckoner.petition({
+  // writ fields
+  title:    'Address vision drift detected at 04:00 UTC',
+  body:     'Drift observed between nexus vision and current codebase state.',
+  codex:    'nexus',
+  parentId: 'w-...',           // optional
+
+  // Reckoner ext fields
+  source:     'vision-keeper.snapshot',    // registered petitioner source
+  priority: {
+    visionRelation: 'vision-violator',
+    severity:       'serious',
+    scope:          'major-area',
+    time:           { decay: true, deadline: null },
+    domain:         ['quality'],
+  },
+  complexity: 'bounded',       // optional — omit rather than guess
+  payload:    { driftId: 'd-123', snapshotRef: 's-abc' },  // optional
+  labels:     { 'vision-keeper.io/vision-id': 'nexus' },   // optional
+});
+
+// writ.phase === 'new'
+// writ.ext['reckoner'] === { source, priority, complexity, payload, labels }
+```
+
+Omitted `priority` dimensions fall back to contract defaults:
+
+| Dimension | Default |
+|---|---|
+| `visionRelation` | `'vision-neutral'` |
+| `severity` | `'minor'` |
+| `scope` | `'minor-area'` |
+| `time.decay` | `false` |
+| `time.deadline` | `null` |
+| `domain` | `[]` |
+
+The `defaultPriority()` helper is also exported for callers building a
+full `Priority` object to override specific fields:
+
+```typescript
+import { defaultPriority } from '@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus';
+
+const priority = { ...defaultPriority(), severity: 'serious' };
+```
+
+### `withdraw()` — cancel a held writ
+
+```typescript
+const cancelled = await reckoner.withdraw(writId, 'Superseded by a newer snapshot.');
+// cancelled.phase === 'cancelled'
+// cancelled.resolution === 'Superseded by ...'
+```
+
+Identical in effect to `clerk.transition(writId, 'cancelled', { resolution: reason })`.
+
+---
+
+## Priority dimensions
+
+The five `Priority` dimensions are designed to be inspectable and defensible:
+
+```typescript
+type Priority = {
+  visionRelation: 'vision-blocker' | 'vision-violator' | 'vision-advancer' | 'vision-neutral';
+  severity:       'critical' | 'serious' | 'moderate' | 'minor';
+  scope:          'whole-product' | 'major-area' | 'minor-area';
+  time:           { decay: boolean; deadline: string | null };
+  domain:         Array<DomainTag>;
+};
+
+type DomainTag =
+  | 'security' | 'compliance' | 'cost' | 'feature' | 'quality'
+  | 'infrastructure' | 'documentation' | 'research' | 'ergonomics';
+```
+
+### Complexity (peer to Priority)
+
+```typescript
+type ComplexityTier = 'mechanical' | 'bounded' | 'exploratory' | 'open-ended';
+```
+
+Petitioner-side coarse cost estimate. Omit rather than guess. Refined by the
+Astrolabe at plan time.
+
+---
+
+## Configuration
+
+Configure the Reckoner under the `reckoner` key in `guild.json`:
+
+```json
+{
+  "reckoner": {
+    "enforceRegistration": false,
+    "disabledSources": []
+  }
+}
+```
+
+### `enforceRegistration` (boolean, default `false`)
+
+Controls how petitions from unregistered sources are handled:
+
+- `false` (default) — log a warning and proceed. Permissive mode for
+  emergent petitioners that have not registered yet.
+- `true` — throw fail-loud with an unregistered-source error; no writ is
+  posted. Strict mode for production guilds.
+
+### `disabledSources` (string array, default `[]`)
+
+Per-source disable list. Petitions from any source in this array are
+rejected by `petition()`. The CDC handler (separate commission) will also
+skip these sources when they appear on already-posted writs.
+
+---
+
+## Kit Interface
+
+Plugins register as petitioners via the `petitioners` kit contribution:
+
+```typescript
+// In a kit's default export (or apparatus supportKit)
+export default {
+  kit: {
+    requires: ['reckoner'],
+    petitioners: [
+      {
+        source:      'vision-keeper.snapshot',
+        description: 'Periodic vision-vs-reality snapshots emitted when the ' +
+                     'keeper observes drift worth surfacing.',
+      },
+    ],
+  },
+};
+```
+
+```typescript
+interface PetitionerDescriptor {
+  /** Fully-qualified source id: `{pluginId}.{kebab-suffix}`. */
+  source:      string;
+  /** One-liner describing this petitioner source. */
+  description: string;
+}
+```
+
+### Source-id grammar
+
+Source ids follow the `{pluginId}.{kebab-suffix}` format — same grammar as
+Lattice trigger-types and Clerk link-kinds:
+
+- `vision-keeper.snapshot`
+- `patron-bridge.commission`
+- `tech-debt.detected`
+
+The `{pluginId}.` prefix is validated against the contributing plugin's id at
+startup. Malformed ids and prefix mismatches are hard startup errors.
+
+### Collision policy
+
+Two `petitioners` entries with the same `source` string are a **hard startup
+error** naming both contributing plugin ids. Mirrors the framework-wide
+collision rule for Clerk writ-types, Spider rig-template-mappings, and
+Fabricator engine designs.
+
+---
+
+## Exports
+
+### Types
+
+```typescript
+import type {
+  ComplexityTier,
+  DomainTag,
+  PetitionRequest,
+  PetitionerDescriptor,
+  Priority,
+  ReckonerApi,
+  ReckonerConfig,
+  ReckonerExt,
+  ReckonerKit,
+} from '@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus';
+```
+
+### Helpers
+
+```typescript
+import {
+  defaultPriority,      // returns the five-dimension default Priority object
+  fillPriorityDefaults, // fills omitted fields in a Partial<Priority>
+  validatePriority,     // throws on invalid dimension values
+  validateComplexity,   // throws on invalid ComplexityTier
+  readReckonerConfig,   // parses guild.json reckoner config with defaults
+  isValidSourceId,      // tests source id against the grammar regex
+  hasValidPrefix,       // tests that a source starts with a given pluginId.
+  PetitionerRegistry,   // the registry class (for advanced use)
+  RECKONER_PLUGIN_ID,   // 'reckoner'
+  createReckoner,       // plugin factory (used by the default export)
+} from '@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus';
+```
+
+### Default export
+
+The default export is the ready-to-load apparatus plugin:
+
+```typescript
+import reckonerPlugin from '@shardworks/reckoner-apparatus';
+```
